In this video, finance chiefs at the CFO Network gathering in Washington D.C. in June discussed their views on cash. Some, like Deloitte CFO Frank Friedman, are holding it as protection. Company attitudes towards cash are conditioned by "the fear of not being able to get it, because liquidity dries up so much that you can't get it when you need it," he says.

Headlines.Author: Steve Gelsi
Headlines.Headline: Flir Systems 3Q Profit Up 9.4%; Govt, Thermography Ops Improve

PARAGRAPH.#text: Flir Systems Inc. (FLIR) said Wednesday that third-quarter earnings rose to $60 million, or 38 cents a share, from $54.8 million, or 35 cents a share in the year-ago period. Revenue rose to $285.6 million from $276.7 million on growth in its government business, as well as its thermography products. Analysts expected earnings of 35 cents a share and revenue of $281 million, according to a survey by FactSet Research. Looking ahead, the company expects 2009 earnings to be "slightly above" its most recent outlook, but it did not release any specific figures. In July, Flir said it expects 2009 earnings of $1.40 to $1.44 a share and revenue of $1.1 billion to $1.15 billion. The Portland, Ore., thermal imaging and camera specialist also said it's buying OmniTech Partners, Inc. for $42 million in cash.
